The paper deals with the problem of generating a computation and communication schedule in a network, which is a topic related to networked computation and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of a packing LP and its dual, which are topics related to distributed computing and optimization, respectively. Hence, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the problem of finding minimum cost embedding, which is related to information theory and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents some approximate algorithms for special classes of graphs, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category as well.
